    "description": "The letter “B” in BlackBerry wasn’t an accident.\n\nLexicon — the agency behind Pentium, Swiffer, and BlackBerry — spent 40 years mapping how sounds make humans feel before they consciously process a word.\n\nB = reliable. V = alive. P, K, G = power and precision.\n\nThat’s why Kodak, Google, and Pentium all hit the same way.\n\nThis is Phonosemantics — the hidden science of billion-dollar naming.\n\nI turned the entire Lexicon framework into a Claude skill called Brand Alchemy.\n\nDrop your startup idea:\n\n→ it names your business like a $1B company \n→ checks domain availability before you fall in love with a name you can’t own.\n\nComment “BRAND” and I’ll send you the link.\n#personalbrand #claudeai #claudecode",
